reviewText:
A truly wonderful experience. To The Moon is not a game but an interactive story, very touching, probably one of the best visual novel I have ever seen (it might be short but it is worth every penny). The 2D old-school graphic is just perfect and the soundtrack is absolutely beautiful.

P.S.
I have to admit ... the story is so emotional that it made me cry at one point ;_;

Post Game Depression;
...the emptiness you feel inside yourself when you complete the main storyline/campaign of a magnificent game and have a brief period of depression where you seem to have no reason to move on with your life..."

I guess it defines To the Moon's experience for me
